Day 9 Topics
1. What is an API?

An API (Application Programming Interface) allows your React app to communicate with a backend server.

Example:

React App
    ↓
Fetch Request
    ↓
API Server
    ↓
JSON Data
    ↓
React UI
2. What is fetch()?

fetch() is a JavaScript function used to call APIs.

Example:

fetch("https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/users")

It returns a Promise.

First Example

Create:

FetchUsers.jsx
import { useEffect } from "react";

function FetchUsers() {

    useEffect(() => {

        fetch("https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/users")
            .then(response => response.json())
            .then(data => {
                console.log(data);
            });

    }, []);

    return (
        <div>
            <h2>Fetch Users</h2>
        </div>
    );
}

export default FetchUsers;
